/-!
# Riesz‚ÄìMarkov‚ÄìKakutani representation theorem for complex linear functionals

This file contains the proof of the **Riesz Representations Theorem** a.k.a.
**Riesz‚ÄìMarkov‚ÄìKakutani theorem** (complex case).

## Main definition

* `ComplexRMK.rieszMeasure (Œ¶ : C‚ÇÄ(X, ‚ÑÇ) ‚ÜíL[‚ÑÇ] ‚ÑÇ)` the `ComplexMeasure` associated to the linear
functional`Œ¶`.

## Main results

* `rieszMeasure_unique`: uniqueness of  `ComplexRMK.rieszMeasure`.
* `integral_rieszMeasure`: that integration with respect to `ComplexRMK.rieszMeasure` is equal to
the action of the linear functional.

## Overview

Firstly the uniqueness of measures satisfying the represenation equation is proven.

The proof of existence of such a measures takes advantage of the corresponding statement for ‚Ñù-valued linear functionals and signed measures (see `Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani/Real.lean`). As such, a major part of the argument is to reduce the complex situation to the case of a ‚Ñù-valued linear functional. Moreover the required measure can be defined using the measure obtained in the ‚Ñù-valued linear functional case.


## Notes

* File destination: `Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/RieszMarkovKakutani/Complex.lean`

## References

* Section 6 of [Walter Rudin, Real and Complex Analysis.][Rud87]

## To do

- Rudin 6.16: Duality of `L^1` and `L^‚àû` (not in Mathlib [https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Lp.20duality/near/495207025])
-/

